The application for the 2023-2024 White House Fellowship is now open. The White House Fellowship program, founded in 1964, offers Americans the opportunity to work at the highest levels of the Federal Government on a non-partisan basis. Selected individuals spend one year in Washington, D.C., working as full-time paid government employees. The program has a strong legacy of producing leaders in various fields. Alumni include individuals who have held top positions in the military, business, education, media, and philanthropy. The application is open to United States citizens who have completed their undergraduate education. The deadline for applications is January 6, 2023. Interested individuals can apply at https://fellows.whitehouse.gov/. More information about the program can be found at https://www.whitehouse.gov/get-involved/fellows/.